\section{Key Code Highlights}\par
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\fi-720\li720\fi-720\lang9\f1\fs20
\bullet\tab lldp_gui.py\tab
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\fi-720\li720\fi-720\lang9\f0\fs22
\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{LLDPScannerGUI} class builds the UI: left pane (interface selector), right pane (toolbar + results treeview).\item Interface selector uses a \texttt{tk.Listbox} with fixed width (25 chars) and functional vertical/horizontal scrollbars.\item Toolbar holds Start/Stop/Export/Columns/Toggle Theme/Clear buttons left‑aligned; a Search \texttt{ttk.Entry} right‑aligned on the same row.\item Results displayed in a \texttt{ttk.Treeview} with columns for timestamp, interface, chassis ID, port ID, TTL, system name, port description, capabilities, and management address.\item No vertical scrollbar on the treeview (removed per request); horizontal scrolling is not needed as column widths fit window.\item Column visibility toggled via a pop‑up menu; widths and hidden state stored in \texttt{self.column\_widths} and \texttt{self.hidden\_columns} and persisted to JSON.\item Dark/light theme switching via \texttt{ttk.Style}; listbox and scrollbars manually recoloured for dark mode.\item Real‑time updates: LLDP callback runs in a worker thread and uses \texttt{root.after(0, self.add\_result, info, ifname)} to insert new rows at the top.\item Search filtering: \texttt{StringVar} trace triggers \texttt{on\_search\_change} which rebuilds the treeview from \texttt{self.all\_results} list.\item Export to CSV writes all currently visible rows (matching any filter).\item Settings loaded/saved via JSON on start/exit.\end{itemize}
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\fi-720\li720\fi-720\lang9\f1\fs20
\bullet\tab lldp_scanner.py\tab
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\fi-720\li720\fi-720\lang9\f0\fs22
\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{LLDPScanner} class wraps a raw socket via \texttt{ctypes.WinDLL('wpcap.dll')} (or \texttt{npfc.dll}) using Npcap.\item Sets a BPF filter for Ethernet type 0x88CC (LLDP).\item Reads packets in a loop until \texttt{self.running} is False.\item Parses Ethernet header, validates EtherType, then walks through LLDP chassis/port/TLV structures.\item Extracts fields: Chassis ID subtype/value, Port ID subtype/value, TTL, Optional TLVs (System Name, Port Description, System Capabilities, Management Address).\item Management Address TLV handling: if subtype == 1 (IPv4) converts 4‑byte address to dotted decimal; otherwise returns raw bytes/hex string.\item Returns a dictionary of discovered neighbor info to the GUI callback.\end{itemize}
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\fi-720\li720\fi-720\lang9\f0\fs22
