\section{Build Process}\par
The batch file \texttt{build\_exe.bat} runs:\begin{enumerate}
\item \texttt{pip install -r requirements.txt}\item \texttt{pyinstaller --onefile --name LLDP-scanner lldp\_gui.py}\end{enumerate}
The resulting executable is placed in \texttt{dist\\LLDP‑scanner.exe}. It bundles the Python interpreter, required DLLs (including wpcap/npfc), and all Python modules.\par
\par
\section{Usage Notes}\par
\begin{itemize}
\item Run the executable.
\item Requires Administrator privileges for raw socket access.
\item Npcap must be installed in WinPcap‑API compatible mode.
\item LLDP is link‑local; only directly‑connected neighbours appear.
\item If no LLDP traffic is present, the idle UI waits until a packet arrives or the user stops the scan.
\item The UI theme persists across sessions via \texttt{lldp\_scanner\_settings.json}.
\end{itemize}
\par
\section{Future Enhancements}\par
\begin{itemize}
\item Add LLDP‑MED (Media Endpoint Discovery) support.
\item Provide a raw‑packet view window.
\item Allow configurable packet‑capture buffer size.
\item Offer 64‑bit‑only build to reduce size.
\item Implement autosave of settings on change (rather than only on exit).
\end{itemize}
